*Singapore Is Said to Plan Local Stocks Boost With Temasek Fund**Time to see resurgence of Spore Mid Caps*New measures aim to support Singapore‚Äôs capital marketsFund of at least S$1 billion will buy local  regional mid-caps(Bloomberg) --Singapore is planning new measures to boost its domestic stock market  according to people with knowledge of the matter.State investment giant Temasek Holdings Pte.‚Äôs 65 Equity Partners Holdings Pte  with a fund size of at least S$1 billion ($745 million)  will invest in Singapore and regional mid-cap companies  including initial public offerings  the people said. Temasek and sovereign wealth fund GIC Pte. will be urged to use the city-state‚Äôs new framework for blank-check companies to encourage or facilitate the listing of tech firms in their portfolios  the people said  asking not to be identified before an announcement expected as soon as this week.The additional support aims to bolster Singapore‚Äôs bourse  which has struggled in recent years with tepid listings and low liquidity. The Monetary Authority of Singapore is also involved in the effort  with the capital markets regulator planning to add to some of its existing measures  one of the people said.‚ÄúThe emergence of innovative  growth companies in Singapore and the region will present opportunities for capital solutions to support their expansion ‚Äù Temasek said in an emailed response to Bloomberg queries. ‚ÄúTemasek and its network of partners can be providers of catalytic capital  particularly in the areas of the longer term structural trends we have identified: digitisation  sustainable living  longer lifespans and the future of consumption.‚ÄùThe Ministry of Trade and Industry  MAS  GIC and Singapore Exchange Ltd. declined to comment.
